text: The 2014 New Zealand general election took place on Saturday 20 September 2014. Voters elected 121 members to the House of Representatives, with 71 from single-member electorates (an increase from 70 in 2011) and 49 from party lists. A total of 3,140,417 people were registered to vote in the election; around 92.6% of all eligible New Zealanders. A total of 2,446,279 votes were cast. The centre-right National Party, led by incumbent Prime Minister John Key, gained a plurality with 47.0% of the party vote and 60 of the 121 seats. ==Notes== ==References== Category:2014 elections Category:2010s elections in New Zealand Category:September 2014 events Category:New Zealand general elections
title: 2014 New Zealand general election
